(4, 2, 'Without Island Hopping', 'TERMS AND CONDITION\r\n\r\nCANCELATION POLICY \r\nYou may cancel your booking by notifying the Tour Operator. CANCELATION fees, if any, will be determined with reference to the date on which notice of CANCELATION is received by the Tour Operator.\r\n\r\nCANCELATIONs Made 15 Days or More Before Travel Date\r\nIf a participant cancels 15 days or more before the departure date, the full deposit of the canceled slot(s) may be transferred or applied to the remaining group members.\r\nThe new per-head rate will be recalculated based on the updated total number of participants.\r\nRevised rates will be applied accordingly, and the updated amount will reflect in the final billing.\r\n\r\nCANCELATIONs Made 14 Days or Less Before Travel Date\r\nCANCELATIONs made 14 days or less before the travel date, including same-day CANCELATIONs, are non-refundable.\r\nThe rooming arrangement may not be adjusted, and the original amount stated in the voucher may still be charged, in accordance with the hotel’s policy.\r\nThe group may still be required to cover the cost of the canceled participant if the total number of occupants in a room affects the hotel rate.\r\n\r\nCANCELATION OF SLOTS POLICY:\r\nENTIRE GROUP CANCELATION:\r\nThese policies will be strictly applied. We made it as clear as possible.\r\nEntire group CANCELATION refers to the situation where all members of a travel party, typically booked under a group reservation, decide to cancel their planned tour or trip. This means that no individuals from the reserved party will be participating in the previously scheduled travel, and the entire booking is voided.\r\n\r\n31DAYS BEFORE THE TRAVEL DATES: \r\nMore than 31 days before departure: Groups may cancel their booking more than 30 days before the departure date without any penalty, and a full refund of the deposit will be issued.\r\n\r\n20DAYS TO 30DAYS BEFORE THE TRAVEL DATES: \r\nCANCELATIONs made between 20 to 30 days before the departure date will incur an administrative fee of P1,000. The remainder of any deposits paid will be refunded.\r\n\r\n9DAYS TO 19DAYS BEFORE THE TRAVEL DATES: \r\nFor CANCELATIONs made 9 to 19 days before the scheduled departure, 30% of the total reservation amount will be forfeited. The remaining balance, if any, will be refunded.\r\n\r\n8 DAYS BEFORE THE TRAVEL DATES:\r\nAll reservations made by the group 8 days before the travel dates shall forfeit 50% of the group’s total reservation.\r\n \r\n1-7 DAYS BEFORE THE TRAVEL DATES:\r\nAll reservations made by the group 1-7 days before the travel dates shall forfeit 100% of the group’s total reservation.\r\n\r\nRE-SCHEDULING POLICY:\r\nYou may re-schedule your booking by notifying the Vantrippers Travel and Tours thru messenger. Re-scheduling fees, if any, will be determined with reference to the date on which notice of re-scheduling is received by the management \r\n\r\n14 days before the date of travel, you may re-schedule your trip, with a change in travel destination allowed - subject to availability.\r\n\r\n5 days before the date of travel, you are not allowed to cancel or reschedule your tour or divert it to another destination if you will, in which case we will forfeit 50% of your reservation.\r\n\r\n2 days before the date of travel up to same date, guests cannot reschedule their tour within 2 days up to same of the scheduled travel date. At this point, our arrangements for your tour are finalized, and we cannot accommodate changes without incurring significant expenses. The down payment made at the time of booking is non-refundable. This payment secures your accommodation and for the van and is used towards preliminary arrangements for your tour. Guests who reschedule their tour within 2 days up to same of the travel date are required to pay the remaining balance of the tour cost. This balance must be paid in full.\r\n\r\nRE-SCHEDULING WITH CANCELATION OF SLOT/S\r\nIf your group decides to reschedule the tour for any reason, and some of your companions are not available on the new chosen travel dates, the reservation of those canceled individuals can be used by the remaining participants. Furthermore, if VanTrippers Travel and Tours implements new published tour rates, the new rate for that tour will apply to your group. Your voucher will also be revised to reflect the new rates.\r\n\r\nLOCK DOWN & TESTING REQUIRED\r\nIf the tour destination has implemented a strict guideline for lockdown, requires an antigen test, or swab test we suggest you reschedule. Most of these guidelines will soon be relaxed and local tourism will soon be allowed without testing required. If you choose to re-schedule, we\'ll always be here to help you out. Your reservation will stay as payment until you can finalize the new date, and then we\'ll revise your voucher according to those dates. \r\n\r\nPHOTOS & VIDEOS \r\nVantrippers Travel and Tours reserve the right to use photographs/videos taken during the services or tours without further consent or written permission from the individuals captured in these images. These photographs/videos may be used in various media materials, including brochures, websites, social media content, and more. \r\n\r\nTo protect the privacy of individuals, we will not identify them using full names or personal information without written approval from the individuals themselves, their parents, or legal guardians. If you do not want your image recorded for distribution, please inform us.\r\n\r\nBy participating in our services or tours and failing to notify us, after receiving this tour voucher, of your desire to keep your photograph/video from being used by Vantrippers Travel and Tours, you are agreeing to allow us to use these images. You also release, defend, hold harmless, and indemnify Vantrippers Travel and Tours from any claims related to the use of your picture or likeness.\r\nSAME DAY OF THE DEPARTURE DATE:\r\nThe group shall forfeit 100% of the total full reservation cost.\r\nThe entire group is responsible for paying the remaining payment that should have been collected for the entire group.\r\nThis serves as a penalty for not informing us about last-minute group CANCELATIONs.\r\nThe funds collected will go toward the booked hotel and slots that were reserved for your group, as it may not be possible to find a replacement on such short notice.\r\nTherefore, the group is accountable for covering the entire tour cost.\r\n\r\nADDITIONAL ROOM CANCELATION\r\nAll rooms have been pre-booked before the travel dates if your additional room request has to be canceled for any reason the group will still pay for the additional room regardless of the days before the travel dates.\r\n\r\nAny rooms that are not used during the stay will not be refunded.\r\nAdditional rooms aside from the pre-booked are subject to availability \r\n\r\nDriver Rest and Off-Hours Policy\r\nOn the first day, the van will pick you up the day before the tour, followed by approximately 12 hours of land travel. After checking in at the accommodation and the end of the day\'s tour, please ensure that you have purchased all necessary items and had your dinner before 7:00 PM. The driver will need to rest after this time due to the long drive.\r\n\r\nDuring free time, any additional activities or destinations outside the itinerary using the van are strictly prohibited, as the day\'s tour has officially ended. If you wish to explore further, you may hire a jeep or other transportation from your accommodation to the town or other sites.\r\nPlease remember to treat our driver with respect and prioritize their health and well-being, as they are responsible for your safety on the road. Adequate rest is essential, so let\'s avoid overextending their working hours.\r\n\r\nUNSATISFIED GUEST\r\nWhile we will not provide a refund if you\'re not satisfied due to unavailable circumstances like:\r\n1) when there are too many people on the tour and you can\'t take pictures or\r\n2) when there is a high heat index and you choose to skip a specific tourist spot or you’re unable to take pictures because of the missed itinerary, please keep your expectations reasonable as we are located in a tropical country.\r\n\r\nACCOMMODATION:\r\nThe accommodation provided in the package is not owned or operated by Vantrippers Travel and Tours. However, it has been carefully selected to meet budget travel standards and is typically classified as 1- to 2-star lodging. These are not 3-star hotels or higher-tier establishments.\r\nPhotos and accommodation details are sent to the client prior to booking, ensuring full transparency regarding room type, quality, and expectations.\r\nVantrippers will not be held liable for any refunds—whether full or partial—due to unsatisfactory service rendered by the accommodation provider.\r\nIn the case of power interruptions (brownouts), guests should understand that this is beyond our control.\r\nRelocation due to brownouts is not guaranteed, especially if the affected area is experiencing the same issue.\r\nNo refunds will be issued as a result of brownouts or similar disruptions caused by external factors.\r\n\r\nMINIMUM OF 4pax| 3pax IN A ROOM POLICY\r\nA room must have a minimum of 3 and 4 people. If any in your group request a room upgrade for a couple\'s room, or an additional room for any division, additional payment will be asked for; a minimum fee of P1,000 per person and per night applies and should be included in the computed amount to be collected on the departure date. All beds are occupied by two persons; those who would like to be in a solo bed will be asked to pay an additional fee per person and per night.\r\n\r\n2PAX IN A BED POLICY\r\nAll beds are double beds, and 2 people should occupy each bed. If you want 1 person per bed, we have additional rates per person.\r\n\r\nTOUR INCLUSIONS AND EXCLUSIONS: \r\nThe tour operator might miss declaring some exclusions on the above list, but anything that isn\'t a part of their inclusive package is excluded from the package.\r\n\r\nFORCE MAJEURE\r\nIf the tour destination on the scheduled tour date is experiencing or has experienced and be destroyed or damaged by fire, flood, lightning, typhoon, earthquake, storm, riot, power outages or any other unforeseen events or disabling acts of God, In the event that a tour gets cancelled due to these reasons, we may offer a full refund or you can opt to re-schedule on different travel dates.\r\n\r\nTOURS BOOKED DURING WEEKDAYS AND HOLIDAYS:\r\nWe are unable to make a guarantee that all tourist locations, pubs, restaurants, food parks, and cafés will be open throughout the week due to the fact that some of these businesses are closed on weekdays and holidays. In the event that we are unable to visit any of the destinations described or any of the tourist attractions that are included on the itinerary, we will not issue a refund or give any other kind of compensation to the participants. This is due to the fact that we are unable to control the hours that any establishments are open or closed throughout the week and during holiday, and the tour operator is not to fault for this predicament.\r\nTOUR COORDINATOR\'S ROLE DEFINITION\r\nPlease be advised that the tour coordinator\'s role is different from that of a tour guide. While the coordinator will not provide historical information about each destination, they will:\r\n\r\nAssist you throughout the tour at each location.\r\nAccompany you and help take group or solo photos.\r\nAct as the primary point of contact between the agency and the guests, addressing any needs or concerns you may have.\r\n\r\nIf you desire historical insights at each location, we can arrange for a professional local guide at a cost of ____/day. This fee would be paid directly to the guide.\r\n\r\nITINERARY\r\nOur aim is to follow the itinerary described; however, unforeseen events, traffic conditions, or any other external circumstances beyond our control may necessitate changes in the sequence of the scheduled activities or miss certain tourist spots. If any of the mentioned itinerary\'s visits are missed, we do not provide a discount or refund. We will not be responsible for any missed or canceled flights due to the aforementioned circumstances. It is not the responsibility of the booking client to take appropriate measures so that his/her flight will not be in conflict with our itinerary. \r\n\r\nBAGGAGE POLICY\r\nFor groups with 8 participants or more, we do not permit large luggage or suitcases. Only bags within hand-carry size limits are allowed.\r\nThis policy is enforced due to the limited space in our vans, which are designed based on the number of passengers and available seating.\r\nOur vans do not have separate luggage compartments, so we kindly ask that guests bring only duffel bags or backpacks that can fit under the seats if your group has more than 8 people.\r\nFor groups with 7 participants or fewer, standard luggage is allowed, provided it fits comfortably in the available space.\r\nTour participants are responsible for their own belongings at all times.\r\nVantrippers Travel and Tours is not liable for any lost, misplaced, or damaged items during the tour.\r\n\r\nVAN DETAILS AND PICK UP TIMES\r\nWe sometimes adjust the pickup time to 30 minutes earlier or later than the original commitment time or in rare cases, we change the van in case the original van provided had an emergency case. Our policy is to provide only the final departure details on the day of your departure to avoid any last-minute changes, which would cause delays or confusion.\r\nTOUR OPERATOR RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Tour Provider agrees to:\r\nDeliver all services as described in this Agreement.\r\n\r\nProvide Van details, including plate number and driver’s contact and coordinators contact details, one day before travel.\r\n\r\nAddress any service disruptions or issues within their control.\r\n\r\nCLIENT RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Client agrees to:\r\nInform all travel companions of the package inclusions and exclusions.\r\n\r\nFollow the rules and regulations of each tourist destination.\r\n\r\nLIABILITY\r\nThe Tour Provider shall not be held liable for any accidents, losses, or damages during the tour.\r\n\r\nThe Client is strongly encouraged to secure travel insurance for added protection.\r\n\r\nRATES AND RECEIPTS\r\nThe quoted rates do not include taxes.\r\n\r\nIf the Client requests an official Service Invoice, an additional 12% VAT will be applied based on the total amount.\r\n\r\nA carbonized Acknowledgment Receipt can be provided free of charge upon request.\r\n\r\nShipping costs for any physical receipts or documents shall be shouldered by the Client.\r\n\r\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date below:\r\n\r\nTour Provider Signature\r\nName: Janine S. Gayas\r\n\r\n\r\nSignature: ____________________________\r\n              MAY 06, 2025\r\nDate: _______________________________\r\n\r\nCONFORME:\r\nI have read and understood the terms and conditions outlined in this Agreement and agree to be bound by them.\r\n\r\n\r\nClient Signature\r\nBy: __________________________\r\nName\r\n\r\nDate: _______________________________\r\n\r\n\r\nThis agreement serves as the official booking confirmation. Thank you for choosing Vantrippers Travel and Tours!'),
(5, 3, 'Joiners', 'TERMS AND CONDITION\r\nThe Client agrees to comply with the tour schedule, pick-up time, and itinerary set by the Tour Provider.\r\n\r\nThe Tour Provider reserves the right to adjust or cancel the tour due to weather conditions, unforeseen circumstances, or other safety concerns.\r\nThe Client is responsible for their personal belongings; the Tour Provider shall not be held liable for any loss or damage.\r\nAll reservations and payments made are non-refundable. This is due to the airline\'s strict no-refund policy, as well as the confirmed reservations for hotel accommodations and activities, which are all pre-booked and finalized.\r\nNo rebooking, rescheduling, or name changes are allowed due to the airline’s strict compliance policies.\r\n\r\nClient Responsibility for Flight Schedule: The Client is responsible for waking up and preparing for their flight on time. The Tour Provider, guides, or drivers are not responsible for waking up the Client or ensuring they arrive at the airport on time. Any missed flights due to oversleeping or lack of preparation will not be the responsibility of the Tour Provider.\r\n\r\nClient Responsibilities: The Client must review the contents of this booking agreement carefully, abide by all terms and conditions, and ensure punctuality, especially for airport schedules and transfers.\r\nForce Majeure: The Tour Provider shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performance due to events beyond their control, including but not limited to natural disasters, government actions, travel restrictions, or airline cancellations.\r\nHealth and Safety Compliance: The Client agrees to follow all local health and safety regulations, including COVID-19 protocols, if applicable.\r\nNo Transfer of Booking: The Client may not transfer their booking to another person.\r\nLost or Stolen Items: The Tour Provider shall not be held responsible for any lost, stolen, or damaged personal items during the trip.\r\nLate Arrivals: Clients who arrive late for scheduled tours or transfers will not be entitled to a refund or rebooking.\r\n\r\nExclusions: Anything that is not specifically mentioned in the inclusions is considered an exclusion from the package.\r\nCheck-In and Check-Out Terms\r\n\r\nCheck-In Time:\r\nStandard check-in time is 2:00 PM. Guests arriving earlier may request early check-in, which is subject to availability.\r\n\r\nEarly Check-In Fee: Additional charges will apply for early check-in requests. The fee will depend on the time of arrival and hotel policies.\r\n\r\nCheck-Out Time:\r\nStandard check-out time is on or before 12:00 PM. Guests exceeding the check-out time may incur late check-out charges.\r\nLate Check-Out Requests: Late check-out is subject to availability and must be coordinated with the front desk or booking agent in advance.\r\nConfirmation of Early Check-In or Late Check-Out:\r\nBoth early check-in and late check-out are not guaranteed and will depend on room availability at the time of request.\r\nItinerary Limitations:\r\nThe tour itinerary is subject to time constraints, and any deviations must be approved by the Provider in advance.\r\n\r\nJoiners Tour Policy\r\nTour Type:\r\nBy booking a joiners tour with Vantrippers Travel and Tours, the client acknowledges that this is a shared tour, not an exclusive tour. This means the tour will include other participants, and all arrangements will cater to the group as a whole.\r\nCompliance with Schedule:\r\nClients must strictly adhere to the schedule and timelines set by the Tour Coordinator or Tour Guide to ensure smooth coordination for the entire group.\r\nWaiting Time: Any delays caused by individual clients may result in forfeiture of certain activities or exclusion from the tour without refund.\r\nShared Facilities and Space:\r\nClients understand that shared transportation (e.g., vans, boats) will involve traveling with other participants. Personal preferences for space, seating, or amenities may not always be accommodated.\r\n\r\nGroup Etiquette:\r\nClients are expected to maintain respectful and cooperative behavior with other participants. Disruptive behavior may result in removal from the tour without refund.\r\nCoordination with the Tour Guide:\r\nIt is the client’s responsibility to stay updated on the tour schedule, follow instructions from the Tour Coordinator or Guide, and remain with the group during activities.\r\n\r\n\r\nForce Majeure and Weather-Dependent Activities Policy\r\nNo Refunds for Force Majeure Events:\r\nIn the event that an island-hopping activity or any other scheduled tour cannot proceed due to weather conditions or other force majeure events (e.g., natural disasters, government restrictions, or unforeseen circumstances), Vantrippers Travel and Tours will not provide refunds.\r\nForce majeure events are beyond the control of the company and are considered as part of the risks associated with travel.\r\nNon-Refundable for Missed Tourist Spots: Vantrippers Travel and Tours shall not be held liable for any missed tourist spots or activities stated in the itinerary due to circumstances beyond our control, including but not limited to:\r\n\r\n-Unfavorable weather conditions\r\n-Force majeure or natural disasters\r\n-Flight delays or cancellations\r\n-Guest-related issues (e.g., late wake-up, sickness, personal pacing, or refusal to continue the tour)\r\n\r\n\r\nNo refunds, rebooking, or compensation shall be provided for any tour components not availed by the guest for any reason.\r\nThe itinerary is followed as closely as possible, but flexibility is necessary to ensure guest safety and comfort.\r\n\r\nItinerary Adjustments:\r\nThe itinerary may be adjusted or substituted with alternative activities depending on the weather conditions during your travel dates. Clients are expected to remain flexible and understanding in such situations.\r\n\r\nExpectations for Tours:\r\nA perfect tour, including ideal weather, seamless timing, and uninterrupted pick-up schedules, cannot be guaranteed. Sudden changes may occur due to weather or other unforeseen factors, and participants must adapt accordingly.\r\n\r\nCoordination Among Participants:\r\nThe success of the tour depends on the cooperation and punctuality of all participants. Delays or lack of coordination among participants may result in itinerary adjustments or missed activities, for which no compensation will be provided.\r\n\r\nSafety First:\r\nDecisions to cancel or adjust activities due to weather conditions will always prioritize the safety and well-being of clients and staff.\r\nResponsibility for Timeliness Policy\r\n\r\nClient Responsibility for Punctuality:\r\nIt is the client’s sole responsibility to be prepared and on time for the designated pick-up schedule. Vantrippers Travel and Tours is not liable for any missed pick-ups due to the client’s tardiness, lack of preparation, or failure to be ready at the agreed time.\r\n\r\nAirport Transfers and Departure Timing:\r\nClients must ensure they arrive at the airport at least 2 hours before the boarding time for domestic flights The tour operator and its staff are not responsible for delays caused by the client’s failure to wake up, prepare, or be ready for the assigned pick-up time.\r\n\r\nNo Refund Policy for Late Arrivals:\r\nNo refunds will be provided for missed tours, activities, Missed Flights or transfers if the client is late or fails to show up at the pick-up location.\r\n\r\n8. TOUR OPERATOR RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Tour Provider agrees to:\r\nProvide all services as described in this Agreement.\r\nProvide the Tour Guide details, and contact information, one day before the travel date.\r\nAddress any issues or disruptions that are within their control.\r\n\r\n9. CLIENT RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Client agrees to:\r\nInform all companions about the inclusions and exclusions of the package.\r\nAbide by the rules and regulations of the locations visited.\r\nBe on time on airport \r\n\r\n10. LIABILITY\r\nThis package does not include airline insurance for both departure and return flights.\r\n\r\nThis package also does not include travel insurance for the land tours.\r\n\r\nVantrippers Travel and Tours will not be held liable for any loss, injury, delay, accident, or inconvenience that may arise during the travel or tour period.\r\n\r\nThe Client is strongly advised to obtain personal travel insurance prior to the start of the trip to cover possible incidents including, but not limited to, flight delays, cancellations, accidents, medical emergencies, and loss of baggage.\r\n\r\n\r\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date below:\r\nTour Provider Signature\r\nName:  Janine S. Gayas\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSignature: ____________________________\r\n             APRIL 3, 2025  \r\nDate: _______________________________\r\nContract Acknowledgment Requirement:\r\nThis document serves as a binding agreement betweenVantrippers Travel & Tours and the client.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe client is required to review, sign, and return this agreement to formally acknowledge acceptance of the terms and conditions.\r\n\r\n\r\nFailure to return a signed copy shall be deemed as implicit agreement to all terms and conditions stated herein, and the booking will be processed accordingly under these guidelines.\r\n\r\nClient Signature\r\nBy: __________________________\r\nName: Jerome Christopher Llagas\r\nDate: ___________________________'),
(6, 3, 'Exclusive', 'TERMS AND CONDITION\r\nThe Client agrees to comply with the tour schedule, pick-up time, and itinerary set by the Tour Provider.\r\n\r\nThe Tour Provider reserves the right to adjust or cancel the tour due to weather conditions, unforeseen circumstances, or other safety concerns.\r\nThe Client is responsible for their personal belongings; the Tour Provider shall not be held liable for any loss or damage.\r\nAll reservations and payments made are non-refundable. This is due to the airline\'s strict no-refund policy, as well as the confirmed reservations for hotel accommodations and activities, which are all pre-booked and finalized.\r\nNo rebooking, rescheduling, or name changes are allowed due to the airline’s strict compliance policies.\r\n\r\nClient Responsibility for Flight Schedule: The Client is responsible for waking up and preparing for their flight on time. The Tour Provider, guides, or drivers are not responsible for waking up the Client or ensuring they arrive at the airport on time. Any missed flights due to oversleeping or lack of preparation will not be the responsibility of the Tour Provider.\r\n\r\nClient Responsibilities: The Client must review the contents of this booking agreement carefully, abide by all terms and conditions, and ensure punctuality, especially for airport schedules and transfers.\r\nForce Majeure: The Tour Provider shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performance due to events beyond their control, including but not limited to natural disasters, government actions, travel restrictions, or airline cancellations.\r\nHealth and Safety Compliance: The Client agrees to follow all local health and safety regulations, including COVID-19 protocols, if applicable.\r\nNo Transfer of Booking: The Client may not transfer their booking to another person.\r\nLost or Stolen Items: The Tour Provider shall not be held responsible for any lost, stolen, or damaged personal items during the trip.\r\nLate Arrivals: Clients who arrive late for scheduled tours or transfers will not be entitled to a refund or rebooking.\r\n\r\nExclusions: Anything that is not specifically mentioned in the inclusions is considered an exclusion from the package.\r\nCheck-In and Check-Out Terms\r\n\r\nCheck-In Time:\r\nStandard check-in time is 2:00 PM. Guests arriving earlier may request early check-in, which is subject to availability.\r\n\r\nEarly Check-In Fee: Additional charges will apply for early check-in requests. The fee will depend on the time of arrival and hotel policies.\r\n\r\nCheck-Out Time:\r\nStandard check-out time is on or before 12:00 PM. Guests exceeding the check-out time may incur late check-out charges.\r\nLate Check-Out Requests: Late check-out is subject to availability and must be coordinated with the front desk or booking agent in advance.\r\nConfirmation of Early Check-In or Late Check-Out:\r\nBoth early check-in and late check-out are not guaranteed and will depend on room availability at the time of request.\r\nItinerary Limitations:\r\nThe tour itinerary is subject to time constraints, and any deviations must be approved by the Provider in advance.\r\n\r\nJoiners Tour Policy\r\nTour Type:\r\nBy booking a joiners tour with Vantrippers Travel and Tours, the client acknowledges that this is a shared tour, not an exclusive tour. This means the tour will include other participants, and all arrangements will cater to the group as a whole.\r\nCompliance with Schedule:\r\nClients must strictly adhere to the schedule and timelines set by the Tour Coordinator or Tour Guide to ensure smooth coordination for the entire group.\r\nWaiting Time: Any delays caused by individual clients may result in forfeiture of certain activities or exclusion from the tour without refund.\r\nShared Facilities and Space:\r\nClients understand that shared transportation (e.g., vans, boats) will involve traveling with other participants. Personal preferences for space, seating, or amenities may not always be accommodated.\r\n\r\nGroup Etiquette:\r\nClients are expected to maintain respectful and cooperative behavior with other participants. Disruptive behavior may result in removal from the tour without refund.\r\nCoordination with the Tour Guide:\r\nIt is the client’s responsibility to stay updated on the tour schedule, follow instructions from the Tour Coordinator or Guide, and remain with the group during activities.\r\n\r\n\r\nForce Majeure and Weather-Dependent Activities Policy\r\nNo Refunds for Force Majeure Events:\r\nIn the event that an island-hopping activity or any other scheduled tour cannot proceed due to weather conditions or other force majeure events (e.g., natural disasters, government restrictions, or unforeseen circumstances), Vantrippers Travel and Tours will not provide refunds.\r\nForce majeure events are beyond the control of the company and are considered as part of the risks associated with travel.\r\nNon-Refundable for Missed Tourist Spots: Vantrippers Travel and Tours shall not be held liable for any missed tourist spots or activities stated in the itinerary due to circumstances beyond our control, including but not limited to:\r\n\r\n-Unfavorable weather conditions\r\n-Force majeure or natural disasters\r\n-Flight delays or cancellations\r\n-Guest-related issues (e.g., late wake-up, sickness, personal pacing, or refusal to continue the tour)\r\n\r\n\r\nNo refunds, rebooking, or compensation shall be provided for any tour components not availed by the guest for any reason.\r\nThe itinerary is followed as closely as possible, but flexibility is necessary to ensure guest safety and comfort.\r\n\r\nItinerary Adjustments:\r\nThe itinerary may be adjusted or substituted with alternative activities depending on the weather conditions during your travel dates. Clients are expected to remain flexible and understanding in such situations.\r\n\r\nExpectations for Tours:\r\nA perfect tour, including ideal weather, seamless timing, and uninterrupted pick-up schedules, cannot be guaranteed. Sudden changes may occur due to weather or other unforeseen factors, and participants must adapt accordingly.\r\n\r\nCoordination Among Participants:\r\nThe success of the tour depends on the cooperation and punctuality of all participants. Delays or lack of coordination among participants may result in itinerary adjustments or missed activities, for which no compensation will be provided.\r\n\r\nSafety First:\r\nDecisions to cancel or adjust activities due to weather conditions will always prioritize the safety and well-being of clients and staff.\r\nResponsibility for Timeliness Policy\r\n\r\nClient Responsibility for Punctuality:\r\nIt is the client’s sole responsibility to be prepared and on time for the designated pick-up schedule. Vantrippers Travel and Tours is not liable for any missed pick-ups due to the client’s tardiness, lack of preparation, or failure to be ready at the agreed time.\r\n\r\nAirport Transfers and Departure Timing:\r\nClients must ensure they arrive at the airport at least 2 hours before the boarding time for domestic flights The tour operator and its staff are not responsible for delays caused by the client’s failure to wake up, prepare, or be ready for the assigned pick-up time.\r\n\r\nNo Refund Policy for Late Arrivals:\r\nNo refunds will be provided for missed tours, activities, Missed Flights or transfers if the client is late or fails to show up at the pick-up location.\r\n\r\n8. TOUR OPERATOR RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Tour Provider agrees to:\r\nProvide all services as described in this Agreement.\r\nProvide the Tour Guide details, and contact information, one day before the travel date.\r\nAddress any issues or disruptions that are within their control.\r\n\r\n9. CLIENT RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nThe Client agrees to:\r\nInform all companions about the inclusions and exclusions of the package.\r\nAbide by the rules and regulations of the locations visited.\r\nBe on time on airport \r\n\r\n10. LIABILITY\r\nThis package does not include airline insurance for both departure and return flights.\r\n\r\nThis package also does not include travel insurance for the land tours.\r\n\r\nVantrippers Travel and Tours will not be held liable for any loss, injury, delay, accident, or inconvenience that may arise during the travel or tour period.\r\n\r\nThe Client is strongly advised to obtain personal travel insurance prior to the start of the trip to cover possible incidents including, but not limited to, flight delays, cancellations, accidents, medical emergencies, and loss of baggage.\r\n\r\n\r\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date below:\r\nTour Provider Signature\r\nName:  Janine S. Gayas\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSignature: ____________________________\r\n             APRIL 3, 2025  \r\nDate: _______________________________\r\nContract Acknowledgment Requirement:\r\nThis document serves as a binding agreement betweenVantrippers Travel & Tours and the client.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe client is required to review, sign, and return this agreement to formally acknowledge acceptance of the terms and conditions.\r\n\r\n\r\nFailure to return a signed copy shall be deemed as implicit agreement to all terms and conditions stated herein, and the booking will be processed accordingly under these guidelines.\r\n\r\nClient Signature\r\nBy: __________________________\r\nName: Jerome Christopher Llagas\r\nDate: ___________________________'),
